rs College Programming CouncilProgramming Council Members 2016-17 Housing Honor Societies at UNT ResearchUNT Undergraduate Research Fellowship McNair Scholars University Scholars Day Eagle Feather Honors Research Poster Print Request McNair ScholarsProgram Information2015 - 2016 Faculty Mentors Advisory Board 2017 McNair ConferenceGeneral Information Conference Program Updates & Announcements Daily Schedule Speakers & Panels Graduate Recruitment Fair Local Transportation Explore UNT & Denton Contact Us Current ScholarsForms Staff Contact McNair Terry Scholars AlumniUpdate Your Information Events & Updates Alumni Spotlights Support the Honors College Contact Us Academics The Honors College is the focal point of academic excellence at UNT. Joining the Honors College gives you an opportunity to be part of a community of scholars united in the pursuit of learning. The Honors College is truly in the business of providing superior learning opportunities for talented students. Many benefits flow to students in the Honors College, but the heart of the program is the honors classroom where accomplished faculty scholars lead talented students toward the highest levels of learning. Another benefit you will enjoy as a member of UNT's Honors College is priority registration for classes, allowing you to register before other undergraduate students. Priority registration is the 24 hour period prior to Early registration. Advising is available to you through the Honors College, and the academic counselor will be glad to meet with you to discuss your academic progress and ways to complete your Honors College award. To make an appointment with Sean Ryan, the UNT Honors Senior Academic Counselor, please call the Honors College office at (940) 565-3305. Get an advising appointment Registering for classes Graduation Visit Us Sage Hall Room 229 Denton, TX 76203 Mail Us University of North Texas Honors College 1155 Union Circle #310529 Denton, TX 76203 Contact Us 940-565-3305 HonorsColleg